org.epochx.tools.eval
Class BrainfuckInterpreter

java.lang.Object
  org.epochx.tools.eval.BrainfuckInterpreter
All Implemented Interfaces:
Interpreter
public class BrainfuckInterpreter
extends java.lang.Object
implements Interpreter

A BrainfuckInterpreter provides the facility to execute programs in the esoteric Brainfuck programming language. Memory is provided in the form of a 30,000 element byte array which the programs manipulate. The eval interpreter functions are not supported since Brainfuck provides no expressions that can be evaluated. The exec methods should be used, with the memory retrievable after execution. The argValues given to the exec methods will be used to populate the first elements of the memory array in sequence. The argNames array is not used.

Supported language syntax

Syntax Effect
< Increments the pointer. The pointer wraps around to 0 if it is to become larger than the memory capacity.
> Decrements the pointer. The pointer wraps around to point to the last memory address if it would otherwise become negative.
+ Increments the value of the memory location addressed by the current pointer.
- Decrements the value of the memory location addressed by the current pointer.
, Not currently supported.
. Not currently supported.
[ If value of current memory location is 0 then jump forward to matching ']'.
] Jump back to just before matching '['.

Not currently supported by BrainfuckInterpreter. Calling will throw an IllegalStateException.

Specified by:
eval in interface Interpreter
Parameters:
program - the expression string that is to be evaluated multple times.
argNames - an array of arguments that each of the sets of argValues should be assigned to. The array should have equal length to the argValues array.
argValues - argument values to be assigned to the specified argument names. Each element is an array of argument values for one evaluation. As such there should be argValues.length evaluations and argValues.length elements in the returned Object array. The array should also have equal length to the argNames array.
Returns:
an array of objects which are the return values from evaluating the expression with each set of argument values. The type of the returned Objects may vary from program to program.

exec

public void exec(java.lang.String program,
                 java.lang.String[] argNames,
                 java.lang.Object[] argValues)
Executes the given Brainfuck program upon the memory byte array. The given argValues will be used to populate the first elements of the memory array in sequence. All other elements of the memory array will be set to 0 byte and the pointer will also be reset to address 0 before execution. The argNames argument is not used.

Specified by:
exec in interface Interpreter
Parameters:
program - a valid Brainfuck program that is to be executed
argNames - not used in this implementation
argValues - an array of values which can be considered the inputs to the program. They will populate the first elements of the memory array in sequence before execution starts.

exec

public void exec(java.lang.String program,
                 java.lang.String[] argNames,
                 java.lang.Object[][] argValues)
Executes the given Brainfuck program multiple times with each of the given arrays of values. Each time the program is executed the memory will setup with the next set of variable values as given by the 2-dimensional argValues array.

Specified by:
exec in interface Interpreter
Parameters:
program - a valid Brainfuck program that is to be executed multiple times
argNames - not used in this implementation
argValues - an array of value arrays, which can be considered the inputs to the program on each call. They will populate the first elements of the memory array in sequence each time before execution starts.

getMemory

public byte[] getMemory()
Returns the byte array which is providing indexed memory for the programs. The array will be cleared for each execution.

Returns:
the program's indexed memory.
